main event: Reports of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) observed in Seattle, Washington, during the 1950s.
interesting points: Observations included round reddish-white and yellowish-white objects,Length of observations ranged from 1 to 3 minutes,Conclusions were often marked as 'insufficient data for evaluation',Various descriptions mentioned objects moving at high speeds and curving,Reports were submitted by both civilians and military personnel.
witness description: A clerk, age 29, reportedly observed the phenomenon through a telescope.
